---
import ProjectLayout from "../../layouts/ProjectLayout.astro";

const frontmatter = {
  title: "Learning Neovim",
  status: "In Progress",
  statusType: "ongoing",
  origin: "Personal Development",
  date: "2025.12",
  techStack: ["Neovim", "Lua", "NvChad", "LSP", "Treesitter"],
};

// Keyboard lighting scheme for learning vim motions
const keyGroups = [
  {
    keys: ["H", "J", "K", "L", "%", "*"],
    color: "#ef4444",
    colorName: "Red",
    purpose: "Movement",
    description: "Navigate text. HJKL for directions, % for matching brackets, * to search word under cursor.",
  },
  {
    keys: ["I", "A", "O", "R"],
    color: "#22c55e",
    colorName: "Green",
    purpose: "Insert/Action",
    description: "Enter \"typing\" mode. Green means go; start inserting text.",
  },
  {
    keys: ["D", "Y", "P", "C", "&"],
    color: "#eab308",
    colorName: "Yellow",
    purpose: "Verbs",
    description: "Delete, Yank (copy), Put (paste), Change, & (repeat substitution). The action words.",
  },
  {
    keys: ["W", "B", "E", "0", "$"],
    color: "#3b82f6",
    colorName: "Blue",
    purpose: "Nouns/Objects",
    description: "Word, Back, End-of-word, Start/End of line. What you act on.",
  },
  {
    keys: ["Esc", "Caps‚ÜíEsc", "Ctrl"],
    color: "#06b6d4",
    colorName: "Cyan",
    purpose: "Escape & Modifiers",
    description: "Caps Lock remapped to Esc (no hand stretching). Ctrl for combos.",
  },
];

// Vim grammar examples
const grammarExamples = [
  { command: "dw", meaning: "Delete Word", verb: "d", noun: "w" },
  { command: "ci\"", meaning: "Change Inside quotes", verb: "c", noun: "i\"" },
  { command: "yy", meaning: "Yank (copy) line", verb: "y", noun: "y" },
  { command: "d$", meaning: "Delete to end of line", verb: "d", noun: "$" },
  { command: "ct)", meaning: "Change To )", verb: "c", noun: "t)" },
];
---

<ProjectLayout frontmatter={frontmatter}>
  <h2>// Overview</h2>
  <p>
    Mastering modal editing and building a custom Lua-based Neovim configuration. The goal is to create an efficient,
    keyboard-driven development environment that enhances productivity across all programming languages.
  </p>

  <!-- The Spark -->
  <h2>// The Spark</h2>
  <p>
    Watching programmers on YouTube use Neovim effectively was mesmerizing. Fuzzy finding files with Telescope,
    harpooning between buffers, zipping around codebases; deleting, replacing, and refactoring at lightning speed.
    It looked like magic. The efficiency gap between watching them work and my own workflow felt enormous.
  </p>
  <p>
    Learning has been difficult. Modal editing is a complete paradigm shift, and building muscle memory takes time.
    But once things start clicking, editing simple files becomes genuinely fun. Going back to nano and scrolling
    through a config file or YAML feels painfully slow now. There's no going back.
  </p>

  <!-- Keyboard Learning System -->
  <h2>// Keyboard Learning System</h2>
  <p class="section-intro">
    Despite typing without looking since childhood, my hands still get confused with vim motions (especially
    remembering where all the funky characters live: <code># $ % ^ & *</code>). So I built a color-coded
    lighting scheme on my keyboard to reinforce the vim "grammar" while learning:
  </p>

  <div class="keyboard-diagram">
    <!-- Visual Keyboard -->
    <div class="keyboard-visual">
      <div class="keyboard-row">
        <div class="key small panic">Esc</div>
        <div class="key">1</div>
        <div class="key">2</div>
        <div class="key">3</div>
        <div class="key noun">4<span class="shift-char">$</span></div>
        <div class="key move">5<span class="shift-char">%</span></div>
        <div class="key">6</div>
        <div class="key verb">7<span class="shift-char">&</span></div>
        <div class="key move">8<span class="shift-char">*</span></div>
        <div class="key">9</div>
        <div class="key noun">0</div>
        <div class="key">-</div>
        <div class="key">=</div>
        <div class="key wide">Bksp</div>
      </div>
      <div class="keyboard-row">
        <div class="key medium">Tab</div>
        <div class="key">Q</div>
        <div class="key noun">W</div>
        <div class="key noun">E</div>
        <div class="key insert">R</div>
        <div class="key">T</div>
        <div class="key verb">Y</div>
        <div class="key">U</div>
        <div class="key insert">I</div>
        <div class="key insert">O</div>
        <div class="key verb">P</div>
        <div class="key">[</div>
        <div class="key">]</div>
        <div class="key medium">\</div>
      </div>
      <div class="keyboard-row">
        <div class="key medium panic" title="Mapped to Esc">Caps</div>
        <div class="key insert">A</div>
        <div class="key">S</div>
        <div class="key verb">D</div>
        <div class="key">F</div>
        <div class="key">G</div>
        <div class="key move">H</div>
        <div class="key move">J</div>
        <div class="key move">K</div>
        <div class="key move">L</div>
        <div class="key">;</div>
        <div class="key">'</div>
        <div class="key wide">Enter</div>
      </div>
      <div class="keyboard-row">
        <div class="key extra-wide">Shift</div>
        <div class="key">Z</div>
        <div class="key">X</div>
        <div class="key verb">C</div>
        <div class="key">V</div>
        <div class="key noun">B</div>
        <div class="key">N</div>
        <div class="key">M</div>
        <div class="key">,</div>
        <div class="key">.</div>
        <div class="key">/</div>
        <div class="key extra-wide">Shift</div>
      </div>
      <div class="keyboard-row">
        <div class="key small panic">Ctrl</div>
        <div class="key small">Fn</div>
        <div class="key small">Win</div>
        <div class="key small">Alt</div>
        <div class="key spacebar"></div>
        <div class="key small">Alt</div>
        <div class="key small">Win</div>
        <div class="key small">Menu</div>
        <div class="key small panic">Ctrl</div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- Legend -->
    <div class="keyboard-legend">
      {keyGroups.map((group) => (
        <div class="legend-item" style={`--key-color: ${group.color}`}>
          <div class={`legend-color ${group.strobe ? 'strobe' : ''}`}></div>
          <div class="legend-info">
            <span class="legend-keys">
              {group.keys.map((key, i) => (
                <>
                  <kbd>{key}</kbd>
                  {i < group.keys.length - 1 && " "}
                </>
              ))}
            </span>
            <span class="legend-purpose">{group.purpose}</span>
            <span class="legend-desc">{group.description}</span>
          </div>
        </div>
      ))}
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- Vim Grammar -->
  <h2>// The Vim Grammar</h2>
  <p class="section-intro">
    The breakthrough was understanding that vim commands follow a grammar: <strong>Verb + Noun</strong>.
    Once you internalize this, you stop memorizing commands and start composing them:
  </p>

  <div class="grammar-container">
    <div class="grammar-formula">
      <span class="formula-part verb">Verb</span>
      <span class="formula-operator">+</span>
      <span class="formula-part noun">Noun</span>
      <span class="formula-operator">=</span>
      <span class="formula-part action">Action</span>
    </div>

    <div class="grammar-examples">
      {grammarExamples.map((ex) => (
        <div class="example-row">
          <code class="example-cmd">{ex.command}</code>
          <div class="example-breakdown">
            <span class="verb-tag">{ex.verb}</span>
            <span class="noun-tag">{ex.noun}</span>
          </div>
          <span class="example-meaning">{ex.meaning}</span>
        </div>
      ))}
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- Motions & Multipliers -->
  <h2>// Motions & Multipliers</h2>
  <p class="section-intro">
    Beyond basic movement, vim has powerful motions for jumping around files and multiplying actions:
  </p>

  <div class="motions-grid">
    <div class="motion-card">
      <div class="motion-header">
        <code class="motion-cmd">gg</code>
        <span class="motion-name">Go to Top</span>
      </div>
      <p>Jump to the first line of the file. Start of everything.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="motion-card">
      <div class="motion-header">
        <code class="motion-cmd">G</code>
        <span class="motion-name">Go to Bottom</span>
      </div>
      <p>Jump to the last line of the file. End of the road.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="motion-card">
      <div class="motion-header">
        <code class="motion-cmd">/pattern</code>
        <span class="motion-name">Search Forward</span>
      </div>
      <p>Search for text. Press <kbd>n</kbd> for next, <kbd>N</kbd> for previous.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="motion-card">
      <div class="motion-header">
        <code class="motion-cmd">?pattern</code>
        <span class="motion-name">Search Backward</span>
      </div>
      <p>Search backwards through the file. Same <kbd>n</kbd>/<kbd>N</kbd> navigation.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="motion-card">
      <div class="motion-header">
        <code class="motion-cmd">:42</code>
        <span class="motion-name">Go to Line</span>
      </div>
      <p>Jump directly to line 42. Or <code>42G</code> in normal mode.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="motion-card">
      <div class="motion-header">
        <code class="motion-cmd">5j</code>
        <span class="motion-name">Number + Motion</span>
      </div>
      <p>Move 5 lines down. Prefix any motion with a count: <code>10w</code>, <code>3dd</code>, <code>2yy</code>.</p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="multiplier-example">
    <span class="mult-label">The Multiplier Pattern:</span>
    <div class="mult-formula">
      <span class="mult-part count">Count</span>
      <span class="mult-op">+</span>
      <span class="mult-part verb">Verb</span>
      <span class="mult-op">+</span>
      <span class="mult-part noun">Noun</span>
      <span class="mult-op">=</span>
      <span class="mult-result">3dw ‚Üí Delete 3 words</span>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- Tools & Plugins -->
  <h2>// Essential Plugins</h2>
  <div class="plugin-grid">
    <div class="plugin-card">
      <div class="plugin-header">
        <span class="plugin-icon">üî≠</span>
        <span class="plugin-name">Telescope</span>
      </div>
      <p>Fuzzy finder for files, grep, buffers. The gateway to navigating any codebase instantly.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="plugin-card">
      <div class="plugin-header">
        <span class="plugin-icon">ü™ù</span>
        <span class="plugin-name">Harpoon</span>
      </div>
      <p>Mark and jump between frequently used files. No more hunting through buffer lists.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="plugin-card">
      <div class="plugin-header">
        <span class="plugin-icon">üå≥</span>
        <span class="plugin-name">Treesitter</span>
      </div>
      <p>Syntax-aware highlighting and text objects. Select functions, classes, and blocks intelligently.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="plugin-card">
      <div class="plugin-header">
        <span class="plugin-icon">‚ö°</span>
        <span class="plugin-name">LSP</span>
      </div>
      <p>Language Server Protocol integration. IDE-level autocomplete, diagnostics, and go-to-definition.</p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- Power Shortcuts -->
  <h2>// Power Shortcuts</h2>
  <p class="section-intro">
    These are the shortcuts that make Neovim feel like magic. Leader key is <kbd>Space</kbd> in most configs.
  </p>

  <div class="shortcuts-container">
    <div class="shortcut-group">
      <h3 class="shortcut-group-title">üî≠ Telescope</h3>
      <div class="shortcut-list">
        <div class="shortcut-item">
          <div class="shortcut-keys"><kbd>Space</kbd><kbd>f</kbd><kbd>f</kbd></div>
          <span class="shortcut-desc">Find files - fuzzy search any file in project</span>
        </div>
        <div class="shortcut-item">
          <div class="shortcut-keys"><kbd>Space</kbd><kbd>f</kbd><kbd>g</kbd></div>
          <span class="shortcut-desc">Live grep - search text across all files</span>
        </div>
        <div class="shortcut-item">
          <div class="shortcut-keys"><kbd>Space</kbd><kbd>f</kbd><kbd>b</kbd></div>
          <span class="shortcut-desc">Find buffers - switch between open files</span>
        </div>
        <div class="shortcut-item">
          <div class="shortcut-keys"><kbd>Space</kbd><kbd>f</kbd><kbd>h</kbd></div>
          <span class="shortcut-desc">Help tags - search Neovim documentation</span>
        </div>
        <div class="shortcut-item">
          <div class="shortcut-keys"><kbd>Space</kbd><kbd>f</kbd><kbd>o</kbd></div>
          <span class="shortcut-desc">Old files - recently opened files</span>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="shortcut-group">
      <h3 class="shortcut-group-title">ü™ù Harpoon</h3>
      <div class="shortcut-list">
        <div class="shortcut-item">
          <div class="shortcut-keys"><kbd>Space</kbd><kbd>a</kbd></div>
          <span class="shortcut-desc">Add file to harpoon list</span>
        </div>
        <div class="shortcut-item">
          <div class="shortcut-keys"><kbd>Space</kbd><kbd>h</kbd></div>
          <span class="shortcut-desc">Toggle harpoon menu</span>
        </div>
        <div class="shortcut-item">
          <div class="shortcut-keys"><kbd>Space</kbd><kbd>1-4</kbd></div>
          <span class="shortcut-desc">Jump to harpooned file 1-4</span>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="shortcut-group">
      <h3 class="shortcut-group-title">‚ö° LSP Actions</h3>
      <div class="shortcut-list">
        <div class="shortcut-item">
          <div class="shortcut-keys"><kbd>g</kbd><kbd>d</kbd></div>
          <span class="shortcut-desc">Go to definition</span>
        </div>
        <div class="shortcut-item">
          <div class="shortcut-keys"><kbd>g</kbd><kbd>r</kbd></div>
          <span class="shortcut-desc">Go to references</span>
        </div>
        <div class="shortcut-item">
          <div class="shortcut-keys"><kbd>K</kbd></div>
          <span class="shortcut-desc">Hover documentation</span>
        </div>
        <div class="shortcut-item">
          <div class="shortcut-keys"><kbd>Space</kbd><kbd>c</kbd><kbd>a</kbd></div>
          <span class="shortcut-desc">Code actions (quick fixes)</span>
        </div>
        <div class="shortcut-item">
          <div class="shortcut-keys"><kbd>Space</kbd><kbd>r</kbd><kbd>n</kbd></div>
          <span class="shortcut-desc">Rename symbol</span>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="shortcut-group">
      <h3 class="shortcut-group-title">üöÄ Power Motions</h3>
      <div class="shortcut-list">
        <div class="shortcut-item">
          <div class="shortcut-keys"><kbd>Ctrl</kbd><kbd>d</kbd></div>
          <span class="shortcut-desc">Jump half page down (centered)</span>
        </div>
        <div class="shortcut-item">
          <div class="shortcut-keys"><kbd>Ctrl</kbd><kbd>u</kbd></div>
          <span class="shortcut-desc">Jump half page up (centered)</span>
        </div>
        <div class="shortcut-item">
          <div class="shortcut-keys"><kbd>z</kbd><kbd>z</kbd></div>
          <span class="shortcut-desc">Center cursor on screen</span>
        </div>
        <div class="shortcut-item">
          <div class="shortcut-keys"><kbd>{</kbd> / <kbd>}</kbd></div>
          <span class="shortcut-desc">Jump between paragraphs/blocks</span>
        </div>
        <div class="shortcut-item">
          <div class="shortcut-keys"><kbd>Ctrl</kbd><kbd>o</kbd></div>
          <span class="shortcut-desc">Jump back to previous location</span>
        </div>
        <div class="shortcut-item">
          <div class="shortcut-keys"><kbd>Ctrl</kbd><kbd>i</kbd></div>
          <span class="shortcut-desc">Jump forward in jump list</span>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- Configuration Journey -->
  <h2>// Configuration Journey</h2>
  <p>
    Learning Neovim also means learning Lua [the language that powers modern Neovim configs]. Before this,
    my only Lua exposure was tinkering with World of Warcraft addon mods nearly 20 years ago. Started with
    <a href="https://github.com/nvim-lua/kickstart.nvim">kickstart.nvim</a> to understand the fundamentals, but
    gravitating toward <a href="https://nvchad.com/">NvChad</a> for its polish and sensible defaults. The goal is
    to eventually build a fully custom configuration once I understand what each piece does.
  </p>

  <!-- Vim Everywhere -->
  <h2>// Vim Motions Everywhere</h2>
  <p>
    Even though I still reach for VSCode often (especially for complex debugging or collaboration), I've installed
    vim motion extensions in every editor I use. The muscle memory transfers. Once you learn to navigate with
    <code>hjkl</code>, reach for <code>ciw</code> to change a word, or <code>dd</code> to delete a line, doing it
    any other way feels inefficient. The motions are editor-agnostic; the habit sticks.
  </p>

  <!-- Why Neovim -->
  <h2>// Why Neovim</h2>
  <p>
    The ability to work entirely from the terminal, combined with the extensibility of Lua plugins, makes Neovim ideal
    for remote server administration and development in constrained environments. SSH into a box and have your full
    editing environment available immediately.
  </p>

  <!-- Status -->
  <h2>// Current Status</h2>
  <div class="status-block">
    <div class="status-indicator ongoing">
      <div class="status-pulse"></div>
      <span>Building muscle memory daily</span>
    </div>
    <ul class="status-list">
      <li><span class="check">‚úì</span> Basic motions (hjkl, w, b, e, 0, $)</li>
      <li><span class="check">‚úì</span> Insert modes (i, a, o, I, A, O)</li>
      <li><span class="check">‚úì</span> Verb + Noun grammar internalized</li>
      <li><span class="check">‚úì</span> Vim motions in all editors (VSCode, etc.)</li>
      <li><span class="check">‚úì</span> Telescope fuzzy finding</li>
      <li><span class="pending">‚óã</span> Learning Lua basics</li>
      <li><span class="pending">‚óã</span> NvChad configuration</li>
      <li><span class="pending">‚óã</span> Advanced text objects</li>
      <li><span class="pending">‚óã</span> Macros and registers</li>
      <li><span class="pending">‚óã</span> Fully custom configuration</li>
    </ul>
  </div>
</ProjectLayout>

<style>
  /* Section Intro */
  .section-intro {
    opacity: 0.85;
    margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
  }

  /* Keyboard Diagram */
  .keyboard-diagram {
    background: color-mix(in srgb, currentColor 3%, transparent);
    border: 1px solid color-mix(in srgb, currentColor 10%, transparent);
    border-radius: 8px;
    padding: 1.5rem;
    margin: 1.5rem 0;
  }

  /* Visual Keyboard */
  .keyboard-visual {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 4px;
    padding: 1rem;
    background: color-mix(in srgb, currentColor 5%, transparent);
    border-radius: 8px;
    margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
    overflow-x: auto;
  }

  .keyboard-row {
    display: flex;
    gap: 4px;
    justify-content: center;
  }

  .key {
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    justify-content: center;
    min-width: 36px;
    height: 36px;
    padding: 0 8px;
    background: color-mix(in srgb, currentColor 8%, transparent);
    border: 1px solid color-mix(in srgb, currentColor 15%, transparent);
    border-radius: 4px;
    font-family: "IBM Plex Mono", monospace;
    font-size: 0.65rem;
    font-weight: 500;
    transition: all 0.2s ease;
  }

  .key.small { min-width: 32px; font-size: 0.6rem; }
  .key.medium { min-width: 54px; }
  .key.wide { min-width: 72px; }
  .key.extra-wide { min-width: 90px; }
  .key.spacebar { min-width: 200px; }

  .shift-char {
    font-size: 0.5rem;
    opacity: 0.7;
    margin-left: 2px;
    vertical-align: super;
  }

  /* Key colors */
  .key.move {
    background: color-mix(in srgb, #ef4444 20%, transparent);
    border-color: color-mix(in srgb, #ef4444 40%, transparent);
    color: #ef4444;
    box-shadow: 0 0 8px color-mix(in srgb, #ef4444 30%, transparent);
  }

  .key.insert {
    background: color-mix(in srgb, #22c55e 20%, transparent);
    border-color: color-mix(in srgb, #22c55e 40%, transparent);
    color: #22c55e;
    box-shadow: 0 0 8px color-mix(in srgb, #22c55e 30%, transparent);
  }

  .key.verb {
    background: color-mix(in srgb, #eab308 20%, transparent);
    border-color: color-mix(in srgb, #eab308 40%, transparent);
    color: #eab308;
    box-shadow: 0 0 8px color-mix(in srgb, #eab308 30%, transparent);
  }

  .key.noun {
    background: color-mix(in srgb, #3b82f6 20%, transparent);
    border-color: color-mix(in srgb, #3b82f6 40%, transparent);
    color: #3b82f6;
    box-shadow: 0 0 8px color-mix(in srgb, #3b82f6 30%, transparent);
  }

  .key.panic {
    background: color-mix(in srgb, #06b6d4 20%, transparent);
    border-color: color-mix(in srgb, #06b6d4 40%, transparent);
    color: #06b6d4;
    box-shadow: 0 0 8px color-mix(in srgb, #06b6d4 30%, transparent);
  }

  .keyboard-legend {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 1rem;
  }

  .legend-item {
    display: flex;
    align-items: flex-start;
    gap: 1rem;
    padding: 1rem;
    background: color-mix(in srgb, currentColor 3%, transparent);
    border: 1px solid color-mix(in srgb, currentColor 8%, transparent);
    border-left: 3px solid var(--key-color);
    border-radius: 6px;
  }

  .legend-color {
    width: 16px;
    height: 16px;
    background: var(--key-color);
    border-radius: 3px;
    flex-shrink: 0;
    margin-top: 2px;
    box-shadow: 0 0 8px color-mix(in srgb, var(--key-color) 50%, transparent);
  }


  .legend-info {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 0.25rem;
  }

  .legend-keys {
    display: flex;
    flex-wrap: wrap;
    gap: 0.35rem;
    margin-bottom: 0.25rem;
  }

  .legend-keys kbd {
    font-family: "IBM Plex Mono", monospace;
    font-size: 0.75rem;
    padding: 0.2rem 0.5rem;
    background: color-mix(in srgb, var(--key-color) 15%, transparent);
    border: 1px solid color-mix(in srgb, var(--key-color) 30%, transparent);
    border-radius: 4px;
    color: var(--key-color);
    font-weight: 600;
  }

  .legend-purpose {
    font-family: "IBM Plex Mono", monospace;
    font-size: 0.85rem;
    font-weight: 600;
  }

  .legend-desc {
    font-size: 0.8rem;
    opacity: 0.7;
    line-height: 1.4;
  }

